254
00:19:01,598 --> 00:19:03,307
Coming!

255
00:19:11,108 --> 00:19:12,692
Lunch!

256
00:19:15,487 --> 00:19:17,697
Ah, what's that?

257
00:19:17,698 --> 00:19:20,908
[sniffing] Worm's wart! Mmm.

258
00:19:21,910 --> 00:19:24,370
And frog's breath.

259
00:19:25,247 --> 00:19:28,791
What's wrong?
I... I thought you liked frog's breath.

260
00:19:28,876 --> 00:19:32,587
Nothing's more suspicious
than frog's breath.

261
00:19:32,588 --> 00:19:37,633
Until you taste it,
I won't swallow a spoonful.

262
00:19:37,718 --> 00:19:39,927
- I'm not hungry.
- [spoon clatters]

263
00:19:40,012 --> 00:19:44,140
- Oops.
- You want me to starve.

264
00:19:44,224 --> 00:19:49,061
An old man, like me,
who hardly has strength as it is.

265
00:19:49,062 --> 00:19:52,982
Me, to whom you owe your very life!

266
00:19:53,066 --> 00:19:55,109
Don't be silly.

267
00:19:56,445 --> 00:19:58,779
[slurping] Mmm!

268
00:19:58,864 --> 00:20:01,908
See? Scrumptious.

269
00:20:05,412 --> 00:20:07,330
[gulping rapidly]

270
00:20:10,459 --> 00:20:14,420
Did anyone think to dredge the lake?

271
00:20:14,421 --> 00:20:16,464
[sighs] This morning.

272
00:20:17,174 --> 00:20:18,591
[indistinct barking]

273
00:20:18,592 --> 00:20:21,636
- Hear that?
- What?

274
00:20:21,720 --> 00:20:23,971
- Shhh!
- [barking continues]

275
00:20:24,056 --> 00:20:27,516
- Zero!
- [barking]

276
00:20:29,269 --> 00:20:31,646
[all yelling, shouting]

277
00:20:40,364 --> 00:20:42,323
Where have you been?

278
00:20:42,407 --> 00:20:45,910
Call a town meeting
and I'll tell everyone all about it.

279
00:20:45,994 --> 00:20:48,788
- When?
- Immediately!

280
00:20:52,960 --> 00:20:58,756
Town meeting!

281
00:20:58,840 --> 00:21:01,509
Town meeting tonight!

282
00:21:02,678 --> 00:21:05,805
- [snoring]
- [Mayor] Town meeting!

283
00:21:05,806 --> 00:21:08,099
Town meeting tonight!

284
00:21:15,607 --> 00:21:17,942
[all chattering indistinctly]

285
00:21:19,486 --> 00:21:21,821
- [gasps]
- [chuckles]

286
00:21:26,159 --> 00:21:27,618
Listen, everyone.

287
00:21:29,329 --> 00:21:33,374
I want to tell you about Christmas Town.

288
00:21:36,378 --> 00:21:39,922
♪ There were objects so peculiar
They were not to be believed

289
00:21:40,007 --> 00:21:43,092
♪ All around
things to tantalise my brain

290
00:21:43,176 --> 00:21:47,013
♪ It's a world unlike anything
I've ever seen

291
00:21:47,014 --> 00:21:50,516
♪ And as hard as I tried
I can't seem to describe

292
00:21:50,517 --> 00:21:53,894
♪ Like a most improbable dream

293
00:21:53,895 --> 00:21:57,523
♪ But you must believe
when I tell you this

294
00:21:57,524 --> 00:22:02,737
♪ It's as real as my skull
and it does exist

295
00:22:02,738 --> 00:22:05,281
Here, let me show you.

296
00:22:06,992 --> 00:22:10,161
- [all gasping]
- Oooh.

297
00:22:10,245 --> 00:22:12,663
♪ This is a thing called a present

298
00:22:12,748 --> 00:22:15,708
- ♪ The whole thing starts with a box
- ♪ A box?

299
00:22:15,709 --> 00:22:17,418
- ♪ Is it steel?
- ♪ Are there locks?

300
00:22:17,502 --> 00:22:20,921
- ♪ Is it filled with a pox?
- ♪ A pox? How delightful, a pox

301
00:22:21,006 --> 00:22:22,256
If you please.

302
00:22:22,257 --> 00:22:25,092
♪ Just a box with bright coloured paper

303
00:22:25,177 --> 00:22:27,595
♪ And the whole thing's
topped with a bow

304
00:22:27,596 --> 00:22:30,681
- ♪ A bow?
- ♪ But why? How ugly! What's in it?

305
00:22:30,766 --> 00:22:32,767
♪ That's the point of the thing
Not to know

306
00:22:32,851 --> 00:22:35,561
- ♪ It's a bat! It's a rat!
- ♪ Will it bend? Will it break?

307
00:22:35,562 --> 00:22:38,272
♪ Perhaps it's the head
that I found in the lake

308
00:22:38,273 --> 00:22:40,900
♪ Listen now
You don't understand

309
00:22:40,901 --> 00:22:44,487
♪ That's not the point
of Christmas Land

310
00:22:44,571 --> 00:22:46,113
Now, pay attention.

311
00:22:46,198 --> 00:22:48,616
♪ We pick up an oversized sock

312
00:22:48,700 --> 00:22:51,118
♪ And hang it like this on the wall

313
00:22:51,203 --> 00:22:54,497
- ♪ Oh, yes, does it still have a foot?
- ♪ Let me see, let me look

314
00:22:54,581 --> 00:22:58,042
- ♪ Is it rotted and covered with gook?
- Let me explain.

315
00:22:58,126 --> 00:23:03,172
♪ There's no foot inside, but candy
Or sometimes it's filled with small toys

316
00:23:03,256 --> 00:23:06,133
- ♪ Small toys? Do they snap?
- ♪ Or explode in the sack?

317
00:23:06,218 --> 00:23:08,969
♪ Perhaps they spring out
and scare girls and boys

318
00:23:09,054 --> 00:23:11,514
♪ What a splendid idea
This Christmas sounds fun

319
00:23:11,598 --> 00:23:14,225
♪ I fully endorse it
Let's try it at once

320
00:23:14,309 --> 00:23:16,769
♪ Everyone, please
Now, not so fast

321
00:23:16,770 --> 00:23:20,106
♪ There's something here
that you don't quite grasp

322
00:23:20,107 --> 00:23:22,525
[all chattering indistinctly]

323
00:23:22,609 --> 00:23:25,861
Well, I may as well give them
what they want.

324
00:23:25,946 --> 00:23:29,490
♪ And the best, I must confess
I have saved for the last

325
00:23:29,574 --> 00:23:32,910
♪ For the ruler of this Christmas Land

326
00:23:32,994 --> 00:23:36,580
♪ Is a fearsome king
with a deep, mighty, voice

327
00:23:36,665 --> 00:23:39,917
♪ Least that's what
I've come to understand

328
00:23:40,001 --> 00:23:43,504
♪ And I've also heard it told
that he's something to behold

329
00:23:43,505 --> 00:23:46,966
♪ Like a lobster, huge and red

330
00:23:46,967 --> 00:23:50,553
♪ When he sets out to sleigh
with his rain gear on

331
00:23:50,637 --> 00:23:54,181
♪ Carting bulging sacks
with his big great arms

332
00:23:54,266 --> 00:23:57,560
♪ That is so, I've heard it said

333
00:23:57,644 --> 00:24:01,105
♪ And on a dark, cold night
under full moonlight

334
00:24:01,189 --> 00:24:06,277
♪ He flies into a fog
like a vulture in the sky

335
00:24:06,987 --> 00:24:10,364
♪ And they call him

336
00:24:10,365 --> 00:24:14,034
♪ Sandy Claws

337
00:24:16,037 --> 00:24:18,205
- [applause]
- [cackles]

338
00:24:19,124 --> 00:24:24,462
♪ Well, at least they're excited
But they don't understand

339
00:24:24,546 --> 00:24:27,006
♪ That special kind of feeling

340
00:24:27,007 --> 00:24:29,675
♪ In Christmas Land ♪

341
00:24:29,676 --> 00:24:32,428
Oh, well.

342
00:24:35,599 --> 00:24:37,766
[animal howls]

343
00:24:42,147 --> 00:24:44,148
Hmm.

344
00:24:51,573 --> 00:24:52,907
Hmm...

345
00:25:05,253 --> 00:25:09,632
There's got to be a logical way
to explain this Christmas thing.

346
00:25:21,269 --> 00:25:26,524
You've poisoned me for the last time,
you wretched girl!

347
00:25:30,904 --> 00:25:33,280
[sighs deeply]

348
00:25:33,365 --> 00:25:38,494
- [doorbell chimes]
- Oh, my head!

349
00:25:41,665 --> 00:25:44,375
The door is open!

350
00:25:45,126 --> 00:25:48,420
- Hello?
- Jack Skellington!

351
00:25:48,421 --> 00:25:50,923
Up here, my boy!

352
00:25:50,924 --> 00:25:54,134
Doctor, I need
to borrow some equipment.

353
00:25:54,219 --> 00:25:57,888
Is that so? Whatever for?

354
00:25:57,973 --> 00:26:01,433
I'm conducting a series of experiments.

355
00:26:01,434 --> 00:26:04,478
How perfectly marvellous!

356
00:26:04,563 --> 00:26:08,983
- Curiosity killed the cat, you know.
- I know.

357
00:26:09,067 --> 00:26:13,279
Come on into the lab
and we'll get you all fixed up.

358
00:26:13,280 --> 00:26:16,031
Hmm. Experiments?

359
00:26:19,119 --> 00:26:21,620
[Jack] Zero! I'm home!

360
00:27:25,810 --> 00:27:30,564
Interesting reaction,
but what does it mean?

361
00:28:25,787 --> 00:28:27,621
[Sally thudding]

362
00:29:00,780 --> 00:29:03,323
[band playing up-tempo music]

363
00:29:09,748 --> 00:29:14,460
You can come out now
if you promise to behave.

364
00:29:15,003 --> 00:29:16,754
Sally?

365
00:29:17,464 --> 00:29:19,173
Sally!

366
00:29:19,257 --> 00:29:23,260
- Oooh! Gone again!
- [lantern crashes]

367
00:29:23,344 --> 00:29:25,345
[chalk scraping]

368
00:30:26,241 --> 00:30:27,658
Oh!

369
00:30:48,054 --> 00:30:50,430
[crowing]

370
00:30:51,266 --> 00:30:55,102
♪ Something's up with Jack
Something's up with Jack

371
00:30:56,938 --> 00:31:00,274
♪ Don't know if we're ever
going to get him back

372
00:31:02,068 --> 00:31:05,070
♪ He's all alone up there
Locked away inside

373
00:31:07,615 --> 00:31:10,576
- ♪ Never says a word
- ♪ Hope he hasn't died

374
00:31:10,577 --> 00:31:13,787
♪ Something's up with Jack
Something's up with Jack

375
00:31:21,713 --> 00:31:24,798
♪ Christmas time is buzzing in my skull

376
00:31:24,799 --> 00:31:27,968
♪ Will it let me be?
I cannot tell

377
00:31:27,969 --> 00:31:31,263
♪ There're so many things I cannot grasp

378
00:31:31,264 --> 00:31:34,308
♪ When I think I've got it
Then at last

379
00:31:34,309 --> 00:31:37,477
♪ Through my bony fingers it does slip

380
00:31:37,478 --> 00:31:39,688
♪ Like a snowflake in a fiery grip

381
00:31:39,772 --> 00:31:43,650
♪ Something here I'm not quite getting
Though I try, I keep forgetting

382
00:31:43,735 --> 00:31:47,487
♪ Like a memory long since past

383
00:31:47,572 --> 00:31:52,075
♪ Here in an instant, gone in a flash
What does it mean? What does it mean?

384
00:31:52,994 --> 00:31:56,371
♪ In these little bric-a-brac
A secret's waiting to be cracked

385
00:31:56,456 --> 00:32:00,876
♪ These dolls and toys confuse me so
Confound it all, I love it though

386
00:32:00,960 --> 00:32:04,671
♪ Simple objects, nothing more
But something's hidden through a door

387
00:32:04,672 --> 00:32:08,383
♪ Though I do not have the key

388
00:32:08,468 --> 00:32:12,763
♪ Something's here I cannot see
What does it mean? What does it mean?

389
00:32:12,847 --> 00:32:13,972
[doll plays a tune]

390
00:32:13,973 --> 00:32:15,849
♪ What does it mean?

391
00:32:16,601 --> 00:32:18,602
- [squeaks]
- [snorts]

392
00:32:21,147 --> 00:32:23,857
♪ I've read these
Christmas books so many times

393
00:32:23,942 --> 00:32:27,152
♪ I know the stories
and I know the rhymes

394
00:32:27,153 --> 00:32:30,030
♪ I know the
Christmas carols all by heart

395
00:32:30,114 --> 00:32:33,367
♪ My skull's so full
It's tearing me apart

396
00:32:33,368 --> 00:32:36,536
♪ As often as I've read them
Something's wrong

397
00:32:36,537 --> 00:32:39,665
♪ So hard to put my bony finger on

398
00:32:39,666 --> 00:32:43,085
♪ Or, perhaps, it's really not as deep
as I've been led to think

399
00:32:43,169 --> 00:32:46,588
♪ Am I trying much too hard?

400
00:32:46,673 --> 00:32:50,384
♪ Of course, I've been too close to see
The answer's right in front of me

401
00:32:50,385 --> 00:32:53,804
♪ Right in front of me
It's simple, really, very clear

402
00:32:53,888 --> 00:32:55,681
♪ Like music drifting in the air

403
00:32:55,682 --> 00:32:59,142
♪ Invisible, but everywhere

404
00:32:59,227 --> 00:33:03,188
♪ Just because I cannot see it
doesn't mean I can't believe it

405
00:33:03,189 --> 00:33:07,359
♪ You know, I think this Christmas
thing is not as tricky as it seems

406
00:33:07,360 --> 00:33:10,946
♪ And why should they have all the fun?
It should belong to anyone

407
00:33:11,030 --> 00:33:14,616
♪ Not anyone, in fact, but me
Why, I could make a Christmas tree

408
00:33:14,701 --> 00:33:18,245
♪ And there's no reason I can find
I couldn't handle Christmas time

409
00:33:18,246 --> 00:33:23,792
♪ I bet I could improve it, too
and that's exactly what I'll do ♪

410
00:33:23,876 --> 00:33:25,711
[cackles]

411
00:33:26,587 --> 00:33:28,088
Eureka!

412
00:33:28,172 --> 00:33:33,010
This year, Christmas will be ours!

413
00:33:33,094 --> 00:33:35,554
[all cheer]

414
00:33:37,098 --> 00:33:39,224
[Mayor] Patience, everyone.

415
00:33:39,225 --> 00:33:42,978
Jack has a special job for each of you.

416
00:33:44,480 --> 00:33:47,858
- Dr Finkelstein!
- [wheelchair whirring]

417
00:33:47,942 --> 00:33:51,069
[Mayor] Your Christmas
assignment is ready.

418
00:33:53,239 --> 00:33:57,659
Dr Finkelstein
to the front of the line!

419
00:34:00,079 --> 00:34:01,621
[cooing]

420
00:34:01,748 --> 00:34:05,083
What kind of noise is that
for a baby to make?

421
00:34:05,084 --> 00:34:07,961
- Perhaps it can be improved?
- No problem!

422
00:34:08,046 --> 00:34:09,671
I knew it!

423
00:34:09,756 --> 00:34:12,758
Doctor, thank you for coming.

424
00:34:12,759 --> 00:34:15,552
We need some of these.

425
00:34:16,095 --> 00:34:22,100
Hmm... Their construction
should be exceedingly simple, I think.

426
00:34:22,101 --> 00:34:25,228
How horrible our Christmas will be.

427
00:34:25,313 --> 00:34:28,315
No. Howjolly!

428
00:34:28,399 --> 00:34:32,486
Oh, howjolly our Christmas will be.

429
00:34:32,487 --> 00:34:35,155
Oh! Hey! [growls]

430
00:34:35,239 --> 00:34:38,158
- What are you doing here?
- Jack sent for us.

431
00:34:38,159 --> 00:34:40,243
- Specifically.
- By name.

432
00:34:40,328 --> 00:34:41,495
- Lock.
- Shock.

433
00:34:41,579 --> 00:34:42,579
Barrel.

434
00:34:43,247 --> 00:34:47,250
Jack. Jack! It's Boogie's boys.

435
00:34:47,335 --> 00:34:51,630
Aah! Halloween's
finest trick-or-treaters!

436
00:34:51,631 --> 00:34:55,175
The job I have for you is top secret.

437
00:34:55,176 --> 00:34:58,261
It requires craft, cunning, mischief.

438
00:34:58,346 --> 00:35:01,681
And we thought you
didn't like us, Jack!

439
00:35:03,351 --> 00:35:06,686
Absolutely no one is to know about it.
Not a soul.

440
00:35:06,771 --> 00:35:09,189
[whispering] Now, you must
go to the forest.

441
00:35:09,273 --> 00:35:11,983
In the forest you will see a tree.

442
00:35:14,112 --> 00:35:15,862
...Christmas Town.

443
00:35:16,864 --> 00:35:18,365
Ow!

444
00:35:19,700 --> 00:35:22,702
- Hmm.
- And one more thing.

445
00:35:22,787 --> 00:35:26,581
Leave that no account
Oogie Boogie out of this!

446
00:35:26,666 --> 00:35:28,291
Whatever you say, Jack.

447
00:35:28,376 --> 00:35:31,044
- Of course, Jack.
- Wouldn't dream of it, Jack.

448
00:35:50,523 --> 00:35:53,275
♪ Kidnap Mr Sandy Claws?

449
00:35:54,193 --> 00:35:56,945
- ♪ I wanna do it
- ♪ Let's draw straws

450
00:35:57,780 --> 00:36:00,490
- ♪ Jack said we should work together
- ♪ Three of a kind

451
00:36:00,575 --> 00:36:02,576
- ♪ Birds of a feather
- ♪ Now and for ever

452
00:36:02,660 --> 00:36:09,082
♪ La, la, la, la, la, la
La, la, la, la, la

453
00:36:09,250 --> 00:36:12,502
♪ Kidnap the Sandy Claws
Lock him up real tight

454
00:36:12,587 --> 00:36:16,131
♪ Throw away the key
and then turn off all the lights

455
00:36:16,215 --> 00:36:19,718
♪ First we're going to set some bait
inside a nasty trap and wait

456
00:36:19,719 --> 00:36:23,263
♪ When he comes a-sniffing, we will
snap the trap and close the gate

457
00:36:23,264 --> 00:36:26,683
♪ Wait, I've got a better plan
to catch this big red lobster man

458
00:36:26,767 --> 00:36:29,895
♪ Pop him in a boiling pot
and when he's done, we'll butter him up

459
00:36:29,896 --> 00:36:33,732
♪ Kidnap the Sandy Claws
Throw him in a box

460
00:36:33,733 --> 00:36:37,360
♪ Bury him for 90 years
Then see if he talks

461
00:36:38,821 --> 00:36:41,573
♪ Then Mr Oogie Boogie Man

462
00:36:42,366 --> 00:36:44,743
♪ Can take the whole thing over then

463
00:36:45,828 --> 00:36:48,288
♪ He'll be so pleased, I do declare

464
00:36:49,165 --> 00:36:51,666
♪ That he will cook him rare

465
00:36:51,751 --> 00:36:53,710
[laughing]

466
00:36:54,295 --> 00:36:55,670
[smacking lips]

467
00:36:58,466 --> 00:37:01,718
♪ I say that we take a cannon
Aim it at his door and then

468
00:37:01,802 --> 00:37:05,555
♪ Knock three times, and when he
answers Sandy Claws will be no more

469
00:37:05,640 --> 00:37:08,808
♪ You're so stupid, think now
If we blow him up to smithereens

470
00:37:08,893 --> 00:37:12,437
♪ We may lose some pieces and then
Jack will beat us black and green

471
00:37:12,438 --> 00:37:15,690
♪ Kidnap the Sandy Claws
Tie him in a bag

472
00:37:15,775 --> 00:37:18,902
♪ Throw him in the ocean
Then see if he is sad

473
00:37:18,986 --> 00:37:22,489
♪ Because Mr Oogie Boogie
is the meanest guy around

474
00:37:22,573 --> 00:37:27,827
♪ If I were on his boogie list
I'd get out of town

475
00:37:29,455 --> 00:37:31,957
♪ He'll be so pleased by our success

476
00:37:33,167 --> 00:37:35,794
♪ That he'll reward us, too, I'll bet

477
00:37:36,671 --> 00:37:38,755
♪ Perhaps he'll make his special brew

478
00:37:40,007 --> 00:37:41,800
♪ Of snake and spider stew

479
00:37:41,801 --> 00:37:45,553
♪ We're his little henchmen
and we take our job with pride

480
00:37:45,638 --> 00:37:48,848
♪ We do our best to please him
and stay on his good side

481
00:37:48,849 --> 00:37:50,725
♪ I wish my cohorts weren't so dumb

482
00:37:50,810 --> 00:37:52,602
- ♪ I'm not the dumb one
- ♪ You're no fun

483
00:37:52,687 --> 00:37:53,687
- Shut up!
- Make me.

484
00:37:53,771 --> 00:37:56,898
♪ I've got something, listen
This one is real good, you'll see

485
00:37:56,983 --> 00:38:00,610
♪ We'll send a present to his door
Upon there'll be a note to read

486
00:38:00,695 --> 00:38:03,863
♪ Now, in the box, we'll wait and hide
until his curiosity

487
00:38:03,948 --> 00:38:07,242
♪ Entices him to look inside
and then we'll have him one, two, three

488
00:38:07,326 --> 00:38:11,037
♪ Kidnap the Sandy Claws
Beat him with a stick

489
00:38:11,122 --> 00:38:14,249
♪ Lock him up for 90 years
See what makes him tick

490
00:38:14,333 --> 00:38:17,961
♪ Kidnap the Sandy Claws
Chop him into bits

491
00:38:18,045 --> 00:38:21,506
♪ Mr Oogie Boogie
is sure to get his kicks

492
00:38:21,507 --> 00:38:25,176
♪ Kidnap the Sandy Claws
See what we will see

493
00:38:25,177 --> 00:38:29,973
♪ Lock him in a cage
and then throw away the key ♪

494
00:38:35,187 --> 00:38:38,398
Sandy Claws, huh?

