00:46:03,594 --> 00:46:06,304
You're right. Something is missing.

595
00:46:06,305 --> 00:46:10,433
But what?
I've got the beard, the coat,

596
00:46:10,517 --> 00:46:12,059
the boots, the belt...

597
00:46:12,144 --> 00:46:16,689
- Jack! This time we bagged him!
- This time we really did!

598
00:46:16,774 --> 00:46:19,817
- He sure is big, Jack.
- And heavy!

599
00:46:19,943 --> 00:46:22,361
- Let me out!
- [all exclaim]

600
00:46:22,362 --> 00:46:25,531
Sandy Claws. In person.

601
00:46:25,532 --> 00:46:27,408
What a pleasure to meet you!

602
00:46:28,869 --> 00:46:33,164
Why, you have hands.
You don't have claws at all!

603
00:46:34,666 --> 00:46:38,044
- Where am I?
- Surprised, aren't you?

604
00:46:38,128 --> 00:46:39,629
I knew you would be.

605
00:46:39,713 --> 00:46:43,257
You don't need to have another worry
about Christmas this year.

606
00:46:43,342 --> 00:46:46,427
- What?
- Consider this a vacation, Sandy.

607
00:46:46,512 --> 00:46:49,222
A reward.
It's your turn to take it easy.

608
00:46:49,223 --> 00:46:53,059
- But there must be some mistake.
- See that he's comfortable.

609
00:46:53,060 --> 00:46:56,813
Just a second, fellas. Of course!

610
00:46:56,897 --> 00:46:59,565
- That's what I'm missing. Thanks.
- But...

611
00:46:59,650 --> 00:47:03,861
You just can't...
Hold on! Where are we going now?

612
00:47:03,862 --> 00:47:06,531
Oh, ho, ho! No...

613
00:47:06,532 --> 00:47:10,701
This is worse than I thought.
Much worse.

614
00:47:10,702 --> 00:47:12,787
I know!

615
00:47:12,871 --> 00:47:15,957
[man] Me on vacation?
On Christmas Eve?!

616
00:47:16,041 --> 00:47:19,919
- Where are we taking him?
- To Oogie Boogie, of course.

617
00:47:20,003 --> 00:47:23,089
There isn't anywhere
more comfortable than that.

618
00:47:23,173 --> 00:47:27,760
- Jack said to make him comfortable.
- Yes, he did.

619
00:47:27,761 --> 00:47:32,181
[man] Haven't you heard of peace
on earth and goodwill toward men?

620
00:47:32,266 --> 00:47:34,517
[all] No! [chortling]

621
00:47:41,942 --> 00:47:46,946
- This will stop Jack!
- [saw buzzing]

622
00:47:55,622 --> 00:48:00,459
What a joy to think
of all we'll have in common!

623
00:48:00,460 --> 00:48:06,215
We'll have conversations worth having!

624
00:48:09,344 --> 00:48:12,471
- [kids laughing]
- Don't do this!

625
00:48:12,556 --> 00:48:15,224
Naughty children never get any presents.

626
00:48:15,309 --> 00:48:17,727
I think he might be too big!

627
00:48:17,811 --> 00:48:19,812
- [moans]
- No, he's not.

628
00:48:19,897 --> 00:48:25,234
If he can go down a chimney,
he can fit down here!

629
00:48:26,486 --> 00:48:29,655
- [grunting]
- [metal clanging]

