00:57:41,583 --> 00:57:43,292
[woman screams]

744
00:57:45,378 --> 00:57:46,920
[both screaming]

745
00:57:47,005 --> 00:57:49,173
[woman screaming]

746
00:57:49,174 --> 00:57:51,216
[screaming]

747
00:57:54,387 --> 00:57:56,430
[cackling]

748
00:58:06,608 --> 00:58:11,111
You're welcome, one and all!

749
00:58:11,196 --> 00:58:13,197
- [phones ringing]
- Where'd you spot him?

750
00:58:13,198 --> 00:58:15,657
Fast as we can, ma'am.
Police. I know. A skeleton.

751
00:58:15,742 --> 00:58:19,828
Keep calm. Turn off the lights. Make
sure doors are locked. Hello. Police.

752
00:58:19,913 --> 00:58:22,498
[woman] Reports are pouring in
from all over the globe

753
00:58:22,582 --> 00:58:25,709
that an impostor is shamelessly
impersonating Santa Claus,

754
00:58:25,710 --> 00:58:29,713
mocking and mangling
this joyous holiday.

755
00:58:29,714 --> 00:58:33,634
Authorities assure us that, at this
moment, military units are mobilising

756
00:58:33,718 --> 00:58:36,678
to stop the perpetrator
of this heinous crime.

757
00:58:36,763 --> 00:58:39,765
Jack. Someone has to help Jack!

758
00:58:39,849 --> 00:58:43,894
- Where did they take that Sandy Claws?
- ... come back and save Christmas.

759
00:58:43,895 --> 00:58:46,271
[alarm sounding]

760
00:58:53,404 --> 00:58:57,282
Look, Zero. Searchlights.

761
00:59:04,791 --> 00:59:06,959
They're celebrating!

762
00:59:07,043 --> 00:59:10,879
They're thanking us
for doing such a good job!

763
00:59:10,964 --> 00:59:15,592
Whoa! Careful down there.
You almost hit us!

764
00:59:15,718 --> 00:59:19,846
- [Zero barks]
- It's OK, Zero. Head higher!

765
00:59:24,143 --> 00:59:26,979
Are you a gamblin' man, Sandy?

766
00:59:27,063 --> 00:59:28,855
Let's play!

767
00:59:29,816 --> 00:59:30,941
Mmm?

768
00:59:31,943 --> 00:59:33,902
My, my!

769
00:59:33,987 --> 00:59:36,655
What have we here?

770
00:59:46,165 --> 00:59:48,417
[whispers] I'll get you out of here.

771
00:59:50,169 --> 00:59:52,671
Lovely!

772
00:59:52,672 --> 00:59:56,174
Tickle, tickle, tickle.
Tickle, tickle, tickle.

773
00:59:58,469 --> 01:00:00,137
[laughing]

774
01:00:00,138 --> 01:00:04,600
What?! You try
to make a dupe out of me?!

775
01:00:06,686 --> 01:00:09,187
[roaring]

776
01:00:12,859 --> 01:00:13,859
[shrieks]

777
01:00:16,362 --> 01:00:18,864
Who's next on my list?

778
01:00:18,948 --> 01:00:23,410
Ah! Little Harry and Jordan.
Won't they be surprised?

779
01:00:35,214 --> 01:00:39,259
They're trying to hit us! Zero!

780
01:00:49,270 --> 01:00:51,855
Merry Christmas to all,

781
01:00:51,856 --> 01:00:55,525
and to all a good night!

782
01:01:06,496 --> 01:01:09,122
[all moaning]

783
01:01:09,207 --> 01:01:11,208
[howls]

784
01:01:15,213 --> 01:01:19,716
I knew this Christmas thing
was a bad idea.

785
01:01:19,717 --> 01:01:22,719
I felt it in my gut.

786
01:01:23,763 --> 01:01:26,431
Terrible news, folks!

787
01:01:26,432 --> 01:01:30,560
The worst tragedy of our times!

788
01:01:30,561 --> 01:01:34,898
Jack has been blown to smithereens!

789
01:01:36,609 --> 01:01:40,320
Terrible, terrible news!

790
01:01:42,615 --> 01:01:47,327
Attention. Attention, citizens.
Terrible news.

791
01:01:47,412 --> 01:01:51,164
There's still no sign of Santa Claus.

792
01:01:51,249 --> 01:01:53,959
Although the impostor
has been shot down,

793
01:01:53,960 --> 01:01:59,840
it looks like Christmas will
have to be cancelled this year.

794
01:01:59,924 --> 01:02:03,969
I repeat, the impostor
has been shot down,

795
01:02:04,053 --> 01:02:08,098
but there's still no sign
of the real Santa.

796
01:02:15,022 --> 01:02:17,065
[whimpers]

797
01:02:20,069 --> 01:02:27,075
♪ What have I done?

798
01:02:27,160 --> 01:02:29,995
♪ How could I

799
01:02:29,996 --> 01:02:33,665
♪ Be so blind?

800
01:02:33,750 --> 01:02:36,835
♪ All is lost

801
01:02:36,919 --> 01:02:40,338
♪ Where was I?

802
01:02:40,423 --> 01:02:47,179
♪ Spoiled all

803
01:02:47,263 --> 01:02:50,682
♪ Everything's

804
01:02:50,683 --> 01:02:54,019
♪ Gone all wrong

805
01:02:54,020 --> 01:03:00,734
♪ What have I done?

806
01:03:00,818 --> 01:03:05,071
♪ Find a deep cave to hide in

807
01:03:05,156 --> 01:03:10,160
♪ In a million years they'll find me

808
01:03:10,161 --> 01:03:13,371
♪ Only dust

809
01:03:13,456 --> 01:03:17,959
♪ And a plaque that reads

810
01:03:18,044 --> 01:03:23,173
♪ "Here lies poor old Jack"

811
01:03:24,383 --> 01:03:27,385
♪ But I never intended

812
01:03:27,386 --> 01:03:30,764
♪ All this madness, never

813
01:03:30,848 --> 01:03:35,352
♪ And nobody really understood

814
01:03:35,353 --> 01:03:37,479
♪ Well, how could they?

815
01:03:37,563 --> 01:03:41,983
♪ That all I ever wanted
was to bring them something great

816
01:03:42,068 --> 01:03:45,779
♪ Why does nothing
ever turn out like it should?

817
01:03:45,863 --> 01:03:48,782
♪ Well, what the heck?

818
01:03:48,866 --> 01:03:51,243
♪ I went and did my best

819
01:03:51,327 --> 01:03:55,497
♪ And, by God
I really tasted something swell

820
01:03:55,581 --> 01:04:00,877
♪ And for a moment
Why, I even touched the sky

821
01:04:00,878 --> 01:04:05,048
♪ And at least I left some stories
they can tell, I did

822
01:04:05,049 --> 01:04:09,678
♪ And for the first time
since I don't remember when

823
01:04:09,762 --> 01:04:13,765
♪ I felt just like
my old bony self again

824
01:04:13,850 --> 01:04:18,228
♪ And I, Jack, the Pumpkin King

825
01:04:18,229 --> 01:04:23,608
♪ That's right
I am the Pumpkin King [cackling]

826
01:04:23,693 --> 01:04:27,571
♪ And I just can't wait
until next Halloween

827
01:04:27,572 --> 01:04:31,825
♪ 'Cause I've got some new ideas
that will really make them scream

828
01:04:31,909 --> 01:04:36,538
♪ And, by God, I'm really going
to give it all my might

829
01:04:37,081 --> 01:04:38,498
Uh-oh.

830
01:04:38,583 --> 01:04:43,670
♪ I hope there's still time
to set things right ♪

831
01:04:44,589 --> 01:04:47,883
- Sandy Claws!
- [growls]

832
01:04:47,967 --> 01:04:50,135
You wait till Jack hears about this.

833
01:04:50,219 --> 01:04:53,555
By the time he's through with you,
you'll be lucky...

834
01:04:53,639 --> 01:04:59,561
The King of Halloween
has been blown to smithereens!

835
01:04:59,645 --> 01:05:05,108
- Skeleton Jack is now a pile of dust!
- [gasps]

836
01:05:05,109 --> 01:05:08,153
Come on, Zero.
Christmas isn't over yet.

837
01:05:16,120 --> 01:05:20,540
What's that you were sayin'
about luck, rag doll?

838
01:05:26,005 --> 01:05:29,466
- [Sally] Help! Help!
- [growling]

839
01:05:29,467 --> 01:05:31,051
Shhh!

840
01:05:31,636 --> 01:05:33,845
[Oogie] Seven!

841
01:05:33,846 --> 01:05:36,932
It's Oogie's turn to boogie now.

842
01:05:37,016 --> 01:05:40,644
- [screams]
- One, two, three, four,

843
01:05:40,645 --> 01:05:43,521
five, six, seven! [laughs]

844
01:05:44,357 --> 01:05:46,650
[Santa] This can't be happening!

845
01:05:46,651 --> 01:05:50,654
Ashes to ashes and dust to dust.

846
01:05:50,655 --> 01:05:55,408
Oh, I'm feeling weak... with hunger!

847
01:05:55,493 --> 01:05:59,204
One more roll of the dice
oughta do it! [laughs]

848
01:06:01,624 --> 01:06:04,459
What? Snake eyes?!

849
01:06:04,543 --> 01:06:06,002
[grunts]

850
01:06:06,003 --> 01:06:08,463
Eleven! [laughs]

851
01:06:08,547 --> 01:06:12,342
Looks like I won the jackpot!

852
01:06:12,343 --> 01:06:15,595
Bye-bye, doll face

853
01:06:15,680 --> 01:06:17,931
- and sandman!
- [screaming]

854
01:06:20,643 --> 01:06:22,060
What the...?

855
01:06:23,854 --> 01:06:26,272
- [shrieks]
- Hello, Oogie.

856
01:06:26,357 --> 01:06:29,192
Jack! But they said you were dead.

857
01:06:29,193 --> 01:06:32,404
You must be double dead!

858
01:06:32,989 --> 01:06:34,572
Oh!

859
01:06:35,408 --> 01:06:36,741
[laughs]

860
01:06:40,913 --> 01:06:44,082
Well, come on, bone man!

861
01:06:44,542 --> 01:06:45,542
[barking]

862
01:06:52,216 --> 01:06:55,010
[moaning] Ha!

863
01:06:59,598 --> 01:07:01,099
Fire!

864
01:07:10,234 --> 01:07:12,485
[grunts]

865
01:07:13,612 --> 01:07:14,654
Jack, look out!

866
01:07:20,202 --> 01:07:24,122
So long, Jack! [laughs]

867
01:07:24,582 --> 01:07:29,753
How dare you treat my friends
so shamefully!

868
01:07:34,467 --> 01:07:38,136
Now look what you've done!

869
01:07:38,220 --> 01:07:45,602
My bugs! My bugs!

870
01:07:45,603 --> 01:07:48,813
[insects continue chittering]

871
01:07:54,820 --> 01:07:56,738
Forgive me, Mr Claws.

872
01:07:56,822 --> 01:07:59,491
I'm afraid I've made
a terrible mess of your holiday.

873
01:07:59,575 --> 01:08:01,993
Bumpy sleigh ride, Jack?

874
01:08:02,078 --> 01:08:06,456
The next time you get the urge
to take over someone else's holiday,

875
01:08:06,457 --> 01:08:08,792
I'd listen to her.
She's the only one

876
01:08:08,793 --> 01:08:11,795
who makes any sense
around this insane asylum!

877
01:08:11,796 --> 01:08:15,173
- Skeletons and boogie men!
- I hope there's still time.

878
01:08:15,257 --> 01:08:17,258
To fix Christmas?

879
01:08:17,343 --> 01:08:21,805
Of course there is. I'm Santa Claus!

880
01:08:26,352 --> 01:08:30,105
He'll fix things, Jack.
He knows what to do.

881
01:08:30,189 --> 01:08:32,357
How did you get down here, Sally?

882
01:08:32,441 --> 01:08:35,944
I... I was trying to...
Well, I wanted to...

883
01:08:36,028 --> 01:08:38,196
- To...
- To help me?

884
01:08:38,280 --> 01:08:40,698
- I couldn't let you just...
- Sally...

885
01:08:40,783 --> 01:08:43,535
I can't believe
I never realised that you...

886
01:08:43,536 --> 01:08:45,995
- [Mayor] Jack! Jack!
- [Lock] Here he is!

887
01:08:45,996 --> 01:08:48,373
- Alive!
- Just like we said!

888
01:08:48,457 --> 01:08:50,583
Grab a hold, my boy!

889
01:08:51,836 --> 01:08:53,711
Whoa!

890
01:08:53,796 --> 01:08:58,675
[woman] Good news. Santa Claus, the
one and only, has finally been spotted.

891
01:08:58,676 --> 01:09:02,053
Old Saint Nick appears to be
travelling at supersonic speed.

892
01:09:02,054 --> 01:09:06,349
He's setting things right, bringing
joy and cheer wherever he goes.

893
01:09:06,350 --> 01:09:09,394
Yes, folks, Kris Kringle
has pulled it out of the bag

894
01:09:09,395 --> 01:09:13,731
and delivered Christmas
to excited children all over the world.

895
01:09:13,816 --> 01:09:16,276
- [snoring]
- [sirens wailing]

896
01:09:16,360 --> 01:09:18,653
[all vocalising]

897
01:09:20,823 --> 01:09:22,323
- Jack!
- Jack's back!

898
01:09:22,408 --> 01:09:24,284
- Jack?
- Jack's OK!

899
01:09:24,368 --> 01:09:26,119
- He's all right!
- It's Jack!

900
01:09:26,203 --> 01:09:27,912
♪ Jack's OK

901
01:09:27,913 --> 01:09:30,415
♪ And he's back OK

902
01:09:30,416 --> 01:09:32,917
♪ He's all right
Let's shout

903
01:09:32,918 --> 01:09:34,961
♪ Make a fuss
Scream it out

904
01:09:35,045 --> 01:09:36,087
Wee!

905
01:09:36,172 --> 01:09:39,007
♪ Jack is back
Now, everyone sing

906
01:09:39,091 --> 01:09:42,343
♪ In our town of Halloween

907
01:09:42,428 --> 01:09:46,097
- It's great to be home!
- [Santa] Ho, ho, ho!

908
01:09:47,725 --> 01:09:50,685
Happy Halloween!

909
01:09:50,769 --> 01:09:52,812
Merry Christmas!

910
01:09:54,690 --> 01:09:56,316
- ♪ What's this?
- ♪ What's this?

911
01:09:56,400 --> 01:09:57,650
♪ I haven't got a clue

912
01:09:57,735 --> 01:09:59,861
- ♪ What's this?
- ♪ Why, it's completely new

913
01:09:59,945 --> 01:10:02,030
- ♪ What's this?
- ♪ Must be a Christmas thing

914
01:10:02,114 --> 01:10:05,116
- ♪ What's this?
- ♪ It's really very strange

915
01:10:11,749 --> 01:10:15,752
♪ This is Halloween, Halloween
Halloween, Halloween

916
01:10:15,753 --> 01:10:17,629
♪ What's this? What's this?

917
01:10:17,713 --> 01:10:19,255
[all giggling]

918
01:10:22,801 --> 01:10:26,012
Careful, my precious jewel.

919
01:10:51,538 --> 01:10:54,332
[Jack] My dearest friend.

920
01:10:54,416 --> 01:10:57,335
♪ If you don't mind

921
01:10:57,336 --> 01:11:00,546
♪ I'd like to join you

922
01:11:00,631 --> 01:11:03,675
♪ By your side

923
01:11:03,759 --> 01:11:06,261
♪ Where we can gaze

924
01:11:06,345 --> 01:11:09,931
♪ Into the stars

925
01:11:10,015 --> 01:11:14,602
[both] ♪ And sit together

926
01:11:14,687 --> 01:11:18,731
♪ Now and for ever

927
01:11:18,816 --> 01:11:22,443
♪ For it is plain

928
01:11:22,528 --> 01:11:26,698
♪ As anyone can see

929
01:11:26,782 --> 01:11:32,036
♪ We're simply meant to be ♪

